IOP treatment led to the inhibition of CPE induced by FHV, which exhibited a concentration-response effect (Fig. 4
A). The IC50 value was determined to be 18.15 μg/mL (Table 2
). In the presence of IOP at 20 μg/mL or 60 μg/mL, viral titers were decreased by 1 or 1.6 log (Fig. 4B). To visualize the inhibitory effect of IOP against FHV replication, a recombinant FHV expressing the eGFP was used. As shown in Fig. S1 in the Supplementary material, we found that IOP treatment reduced the fluorescence intensity, which depended on the dose of IOP.
